1 AN ACT relating to technology in public schools.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 158.165 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) (a) The board of education of each school district shall adopt[develop] a policy
5 regarding the possession and use of a personal telecommunications device by
6 a student while on school property or while attending a school-sponsored or
7 school-related activity on or off school property, and shall include the policy
8 in the district's written standards of student conduct.
9 (b) The policy shall, at a minimum, prohibit a student's use of a personal
10 telecommunications device during instructional time, except during an
11 emergency, if directed to do so by a teacher for an instructional purpose, or
12 if authorized by a teacher.
13 (c) A student who violates the policy shall be subject to discipline as provided by
14 board policy.
15 (2) As used in this section, "personal telecommunications device":
16 (a) Means a device that emits an audible signal, vibrates, displays a message, or
17 otherwise summons or delivers a communication to the possessor, including[,]
18 but not limited to[,] a paging device and a cellular telephone; and
19 (b) Does not include any device a student is authorized to use pursuant to the
20 Individuals with Disabilities Education Act, 20 U.S.C. sec. 1400 et seq., the
21 Americans with Disabilities Act, 42 U.S.C. sec. 12101 et seq., or the
22 Rehabilitation Act of 1973, 29 U.S.C. sec. 701 et seq., or successor acts.
23 Section 2. KRS 156.675 is amended to read as follows:
24 (1) The Kentucky Board of Education shall promulgate administrative regulations to
25 prevent social media and sexually explicit material from being transmitted via any
26 video or computer system, software or hardware product, or Internet service
27 managed or provided to local schools or school districts.
