1 (2) Each local school district and school shall utilize the latest available filtering
2 technology to ensure that social media and sexually explicit material is not made
3 available to students.
4 (3) The Kentucky Department of Education shall make available to school districts and
5 schools upon request and without cost, state-of-the-art software products that enable
6 local districts and schools to prevent access to social media and sexually explicit
7 material. The department shall also notify all school districts and schools of the
8 availability of the software. Any product provided or obtained by a district or
9 school shall meet the requirements of subsection (2) of this section.
10 (4) Each local school district shall establish a policy regarding student internet access
11 that shall include[,] but not be limited to[,] parental consent for student internet use,
12 teacher supervision of student computer use, and auditing procedures to determine
13 whether education technology is being used for the purpose of accessing social
14 media or sexually explicit or other objectionable material.
15 (5) The provisions of subsections (1) to (4) of this section shall only apply to social
16 media that a student is not authorized by a teacher to access for an instructional
17 purpose.
